---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Zahit | About";
const pageDescription = "Zahit is more than just a theme; it is a perspective.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
    <article>
        <header>
            <h1>About Zahit</h1>
            <p>
                Zahit is more than just a theme; it is a perspective. It
                represents a way of highlighting what truly matters by stripping
                away the unnecessary. Zahit is a symbol of doing more with less,
                of finding depth within simplicity in the digital space.
            </p>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h2>Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Clean, minimalist design</li>
                <li>Full dark mode support</li>
                <li>Responsive layout for all devices</li>
                <li>Easy content management with Astro components</li>
                <li>Markdown and MDX support</li>
                <li>Code syntax highlighting for developers</li>
                <li>Tags and categorization</li>
                <li>SEO‑friendly structure</li>
                <li>High performance with minimal JavaScript</li>
                <li>Smooth transitions and subtle animations</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Philosophy</h2>
            <p>
                Zahit sees simplicity not as a lack, but as a strength. To leave
                behind what is unnecessary and bring forward what is meaningful…
                This theme offers creators a quiet space: distraction‑free,
                simple yet profound. Zahit is a pause in the digital world, a
                place where readers meet the text and writers meet their
                essence.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <p>
                Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, Zahit avoids
                heavy frameworks to remain lightweight and flexible. Styled with
                handcrafted CSS, it provides a solid foundation for your content
                while keeping speed and clarity at the core.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>License</h2>
            <p>
                Zahit is open‑source software licensed under the{" "}
                <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT">MIT License</a>.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Support</h2>
            <p>
                If you find Zahit useful, you can support its development by
                giving it a star on{" "}
                <a href="https://github.com/kuscadev/Zahit">GitHub</a>.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Get Started</h2>
            <p>
                Whether you’re a developer sharing code snippets, a writer
                telling stories, or simply someone seeking a clean digital
                space, Zahit is the perfect starting point. Minimal. Practical.
                Worth Sharing.
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
